'''Seoul Subway Line 7''' of the [[Seoul Metropolitan Subway]] was built from 1990 to 1996 ([[Jangam station|Jangam]]-[[Konkuk University station|Konkuk Univ.]]) and was completed on August 1, 2000 (central section {{convert|17|km|mi|abbr=on|sp=us|disp=}}. [[Konkuk University station|Konkuk University]] to [[Sinpung station|Sinpung]]); the western section between [[Sinpung station|Sinpung]] and [[Onsu station|Onsu]] was put into service on February 29, 2000. This north-south line does not run through the city centre but links [[Gangnam District|Gangnam]] directly to the northeastern districts of Seoul. In 2019, Line 7 had an annual ridership of 380 million or 1.04 million passengers per day.<ref>{{Cite web|title=서울시 지하철수송 통계|url=http://data.seoul.go.kr/dataList/273/S/2/datasetView.do#none|access-date=2021-05-21|website=data.seoul.go.kr|language=ko}}</ref> Although most trains run between [[Jangam station|Jangam]] and [[Seongnam station (Incheon)|Seongnam]], some trains short turn at [[Onsu station|Onsu]] station and some trains start at [[Dobongsan station|Dobongsan]] station.

All trains on Line 7 are monitored by 1,008 [[closed-circuit television camera]]s that were installed in June 2012.<ref>{{cite news| title=Seoul Subway Trains Fitted with CCTVs| url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2012/06/19/2012061901238.html| access-date=July 29, 2012| newspaper=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]| date=June 29, 2012}}</ref>

The extension to [[Incheon Subway Line 1]] was designed to relieve the traffic congestion in western Seoul and northern Incheon. Nine stations were added on October 27, 2012, for the {{convert|10.2|km|mi|abbr=on|sp=us|disp=}} extension, starting from [[Onsu Station]] of Line 7 and ending at [[Bupyeong-gu Office Station]] of [[Incheon Subway Line 1]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2005-03-04 |title=[수도권]지하철7호선 연장구간 착공 |url=https://www.donga.com/news/article/all/20050304/8165794/1 |access-date=2024-08-01 |website=동아일보 |language=ko}}</ref>

Line 7 was extended west of Bupyeong-gu Office. Construction on the two-station, {{convert|3.94|km|mi|abbr=on|sp=us|disp=}} extension to [[Seongnam station (Incheon)|Seongnam]] began in 2013 and was completed on May 22, 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |title=사업소개 |url=http://www.incheon.go.kr/icweb/html/web15/015001001003.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130111234841/http://www.incheon.go.kr/icweb/html/web15/015001001003.html |archive-date=January 11, 2013 |access-date=June 7, 2012 |publisher=도시철도건설본부 |language=ko}}</ref> The extension allows for transfers to [[Incheon Subway Line 2]].

== Expansion ==
A further seven-station extension to [[Cheongna International City station]] through Cheongna International City is currently planned and is not expected to open any earlier than 2027; the extension will allow for transfers to [[A'REX|the airport railroad]]. Another further two-station extension through Incheon's metropolitan landfill to [[Geomdan Oryu station]] is also currently being planned.

Line 7 is also being extended north of Jangam to Yangju and Pocheon in two phases. The first phase, which started construction in late 2019 and is planned to open in 2027,{{Citation needed|date=June 2026}} will feature two stations, one of which will be [[Tapseok station]], providing transfers to the [[Uijeongbu LRT]]. The second phase, which is still in planning, will feature four additional stations. The second phase may be operated as a shuttle service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.edaily.co.kr/news/Read?newsId=03873686625996880&mediaCodeNo=257&OutLnkChk=Y|title = 경기도, '예타면제 7호선 포천연장' 규모 축소…포천시민 뿔났다|date = 9 December 2020}}</ref>

== Operation ==
Although the line is mostly operated by [[Seoul Metro]], the section beyond [[Onsu Station|Onsu]], between [[Kkachiul Station|Kkachiul]] and [[Seongnam Station (Incheon)|Seongnam]] (including the future extension to [[Cheongna International City station|Cheongna Int'l City]]) is operated by [[Incheon Transit Corporation]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Operation Overview |url=https://www.ictr.or.kr/main/railway/intro.jsp |website=Incheon Metro |access-date=7 August 2024}}</ref> Further, this section was funded as Bucheon and Incheon City metro, is considered a part of [[Incheon Metro]] rather than as a part of Seoul Subway, and serves as an east-west line through wider Incheon area.

Despite this, the entire line is operated as one, with all trains in the Incheon-operated section continuing onto the Seoul-operated section. Approximately half of trains in the Seoul-operated section continue onto the Incheon-operated section.<ref>Line 7 Timetable, from [http://www.seoulmetro.co.kr/kr/cyberStation.do Seoul Metro Cyber Station]</ref>

